    "section_xLfeJm": {
      "type": "section",
      "blocks": {
        "text_NeWBXt": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Traditional manufacturing is a game of waste—massive molds, thousands of unsold items sitting in warehouses, and scraps left on the factory floor. We do things differently. We use <strong>Additive Manufacturing</strong>, a process where your product is built layer-by-layer, only using the exact amount of material needed. This 'on-demand' model means we don't overproduce, and we can achieve complex, organic geometries that are physically impossible to create any other way.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "none",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
